author: {'steamid': '76561198210919148', 'num_games_owned': 164, 'num_reviews': 36, 'playtime_forever': 21, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20, 'last_played': 1674316136}
review:
If Counter-Strike and Diep.io had a child but punched the fucking fetus, this would be it.
What the fuck, is this game supposed to be?
I mean, I like that it has a lot of content, there's many weapons, and there's many game modes.
But, after having tried all of those game modes, guess how many players I found?
ONE. One singular player.
On top of that, the game is laggy as fuck in terms of ping.
And the controls feel clunky in my opinion.
Maybe this game was fun when it wasn't dead, but it appears to me like it's a rip off of Diep.io
Waste of space, don't even bother installing this.

review:
Strike.is The Game is a mobile/browser game that got dumped on Steam, for no apparent reason apart from to reduce the average quality of games on Steam. 

Gameplay is PvP only.  You control a 2D retro pixel gun surrounded by a flat circle. 

It's actually more entertaining trying to imagine who thought this would be a fun idea for a game than actually playing this browser garbage.  People are aware 3D graphics exist, right?  You can play TF2 and dozens of other excellent FPS PvP games for free...

author: {'steamid': '76561198171846557', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 317, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 317, 'last_played': 1489887290}
review:
Again, this game is another ripoff of a game from the IO series (the games for your browser, and yes, I said the "IO series"), being the game this time Diep.io, by the same creators of Agar.io and Slither.io. 

So, I don't know, honestly, it's a little shooter game. It's fun, don't get me wrong, but there's one fatal flaw: You can't set your own controls. The controls at default are WASD or you used your arrows. I understand, it's been the control scheme for decades, but for touchtypers like me and some other people, we would like to set our own controls.

The real reason why it's a fatal flaw is because some people aren't familiar with this control scheme, and new people to these controls will not get used to it very quickly. This in turn makes people lose a lot more, hence the choppy controls.

Besides that, there's the re-usage of the music from the other games (Mitos.is and Worm.is), which was kind of a bad thing to do since there is no more variety. They could have at least enabled (for all games) to input your OWN music. That would have been very nice and I guaruntee that the games would get more players.

That's really about it, considering the game is very fluid compared to Diep.io. I have mixed feelings about this one, so in total, [i]5/10[/i].

Fun to play! although this game is terrible at currency, it took 2 days to get my first bought item. honestly, this company needs to ACTUALLY IMPROVE! by making it easier to get coins and lowering the prices if you dont make it easier, its boring without cool stuff, even in TF2 its easier to get items! let us actually play for the money! NOT WAIT FOR IT! and its not live either! ie: money = 50, goes back into game and picks up another coin, money still = 50. WHAT?! this is not how games work!!! the reason im recommending this is because of how fun it is. but still. this game's currency system is about 150-250 coins per day. 5 - 25 coins per hour! ugh, i would play this constantly if it had a better currency system. overall - gameplay = awesome | maps = cool | music = could use some work | currency = crap | gamemodes = eh.
there you go, my review for Strike.Is (mostly complains about currency.)

PD : SE ME HABIA OLVIDADO DECIR QUE CUANDO REAPARECES TIENE EL MISMO SONIDO QUE EN OVERWATCH.

review:
I'd like to point out that in addition to the bad controls, the game rips off a number of features from a new Class-Based Multiplayer game which shall not be named. Each weapon gives you attributes that essentially make you your own class. For example:

[list]
[*] A short-range plasma rifle which lets you 'Blink' forward every few seconds
[*] A rifle that gives you the abilities 'Run' and [b]'Biotic Field Generator' [/b]
[*] A double-barreled shotgun that gives you a 'Healing Potion' which recharges every 12 seconds
[*] Long-range dual pistols with an ability to run and shoot 6 bullets rapidly
[*] A laser gun that gives you the ability to place a 'Magnetic Shield' around yourself
[*] A grenade launcher with the abilities 'Remote Detonate' and 'Frag Jump'
[*] A sniper rifle allowing 'Sniper Sight'
[*] A crossbow that shoots arrows but also has a 'Bouncing Shot' ability
[*]
[/list]

review: I personally enjoyed the other games, taking the simple mechanics of agar.io and slither.io and expanding upon them, whilst making it easier to play, as they would have tremendous lag when playing in browser. They personally helped me and made a simple concept better (maybe). But this sh*tty, rushed bullsh*t topped off with clunky controls and lag is a shameless cash in involving no effort what so ever. I only played this game for a short time, but boy it was hard not to quit immediately. Don't even bother downloading this garbage. I reccomend the other remakes made by this developer, but avoid this one at all costs.

review: So you wouldnt expect much from a simple free steam game like this, BUT its really addicting and fun to play. The game has a money system and best of all you can pick up weapons from the ground! So even if your a low level you'll still have all the guns as the higher levels. The only diffrence is people who have played longer obviously have more money so they spawn with better weapons if my understanding of this game is correct. I really reccomend this game its actually really fun and its not that big of a game, its only like 100MB or something.

review:
this is just another game trying to cash in on the craze Agar.io started. it feels that the name alone can entice players into playing it. Won't lie, it's somewhat enjoyable sometimes, but regardless the lack of love put into this game on the dev side shows.

If you like it, great. to me, and probably to many others, it's mediocre at best, tedius and dare I say one sided at worst. the characters are far too slow to allow any true feeling of action nor skill. TDM can become and stay very one-sided with the first team to pin down the other getting access to the best of the best weapons.

And, of course, boring AF, to me at least. Again, if you like it, great. I'm glad you can see something in this that I can't. This just, really is not for me.

"Strike.is? More lik ISIS, AMIRIGHT?" - XkewldudeX

author: {'steamid': '76561198235884198', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 740, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20, 'last_played': 1484859059}
review: On August 23 an update went out that basicly makes it simply load at the title screen forever, for pc users on windows 8.2 and even window ten; the new and best OS right? Reinstalling the game doesnt fix the problem. All the games made by the developers such as Mitos.is- Strike.is and Snake will not load. Simply at this point the IOS users are quite enjoying the games alone. Which is quite weird or an eye opener that a competive update came out for "everyone"; but however IOS users are only able to compete. SO is it intentional or not? Multiple users for pc are having a problem; while others can compete with a clean slate or at the least with out the competion of cross platform users- Pc. If you on any platform support the games by this developer, you need to look at how and why a competive update came out while stopping the amount of possible players from competing; in logic terms it's simple they needed to unoffically clear some of the players out the way. Some might say "no way they'd be able to do that"; well ask yourself first do you think they will restart it after they fix the problems? "NO way; they cant strip the winnings from the player(s) that did win", even if the devs toke half the playing field away. Good luck to the ones still playing that will enjoy less players. It really doesnt take alot to see that the timing is the key to this lock out of player. It even calls it an update opening more compation to the game with a new season. They are inadvertinly stating that it is a hand over to IOS users to feel grand about the support they are due. DO NOT support this action or the future actions like this. Simply they know what they did and it will happen surely to the communtiy again when season 10 comes. Donations would be asked by the devs to fix these simple "scandals tactics"; which in its self is one correct? Do not recommend to friends and people you like in the real world, you'd only be giving them a shot in the back.

review:
I stumbled across this little game last night while playing Mitos.is. I found it quite enjoyable. Lots of the reviewers are but hurt because they say it is a rip off of some other games, because you know that has never happened before.. dota, league of legends, heroes of newerth, smite, heroes of the storm... it happens all the time get over it.

pros
- fun times
- lots of killing
- variety of guns
- purchaseable starting equipment
- various game modes, Capture the flag, Team Fortress, Death match, and others.

con
- need to remap the W key from moving the direction the mouse is to just UP.
- minor bugs
- needs more maps for game modes

review:

+- schlichte Grafik

Negativ:
- unzerst√∂rbare Umgebung

- nur im Modus "Deathmatch" Erfahrung nach Levelh√∂he des Gegners, wodurch man viel mehr Erfahrung als in anderen Modi erh√§lt, sodass Motivation f√ºr andere Modi nicht gegeben ist

author: {'steamid': '76561198074048831', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 347, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 275, 'last_played': 1515027389}
review:
I read a lot of crazy bad reviews for this game...and unless you are a graphics whore...there is no reason not to love this game...oh I guess maybe it doesnt have zombies either...but lets face it, that whole zombie theme is started to get old.

This is a super solid casual shooter.
It has fast paced action.
It has super smooth controls,
It has guns that make you teleport.
It has retroish top down graphics...the graphics are not its stong point, but they are effective.
Lots of people are playing it so there are a lot of dudes to shoot your teleport gun at.
It is still being updated, which means the game makers give a shit about it.
It has some okayish dance party music.

also its free...so why not try it?

review:
This game is a calamity.

First off, I would like to say I recommend it mostly because its free.
Whats to loose?

It is addicting, and it will keep you full for an hour or two.  The concept is cute and fun, the use of powerups is adorable.

The concept however addicting is also stolen from agar.io and diep.io, they even used the original skins from agar.io (i.e hillary clinton, stalin, ec.) It has low content and quality, but once again its free so I recommend trying it. 


5/10 so average for a free game,

Die paar MB lohnt es sich wenigstens mal reinzugucken, die zahlreichen negativen Bewertungen stammen wohl von wirklich von Usern die sich unter dem Titel ein riesen Spiel mit massen an Kontent und jahrelangem Spielspa√ü vorgestellt haben .. obwohl ein Einsch√§tzen beim ersten Blick auf die Bilder oben nicht allzu schwer sein sollte.

author: {'steamid': '76561198083944846', 'num_games_owned': 387, 'num_reviews': 28, 'playtime_forever': 6, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6, 'last_played': 1469098645}
review:
This obviously started as a tried-and-true-formula sort of thing. It's becoming quite the theme for them to take games about bubbles and cells from websites, steal the whole damn thing, add microtransactions, remove the joy, and rebrand it as their own. Mitos.is = Agar.io, Worm.is = Slither.io, Strike.is = Diep.io. It [i]started[/i] that way. But it seems the developers had a change of heart. They didn't want to have it be a complete clone of diep.io. What would be the point? So they removed the leveling system, removed the tree system, removed smooth movement, removed the absence of lag (my little joke, all their games lag to shit), and added walls and barriers. It's a god-awful game. The other ones were good games, if judged on their own (for the sole reason that the developers straight-up ripped off even better games). This one isn't. 8 directional movement, lag like you wouldn't believe, and [i]barriers[/i], which have no place in a cell game. None. 

Oh, and for bonus ducks, they stole Overwatch's loading animation. [u]What.[/u]

Nice game.

review:
Disclaimer: Me, like many, MANY others, downloaded this game to write a Review.

Disclaimer 2: If you're reading this review about a game that you THINK you might be interested in, and is Offended by this review, Please know that my intent was not to do this. I Apologize if this is the Case, but please, i Insist you read on why this game is a Pile of Wank.

TL;DR: Don't download anything from Freakinware. They're Copycat F*cknuggets riding on the Hype train that are Agar.io, Slither.io, and Diep.io.

[h1]What is this Game?[/h1]

This "[i]game[/i]" is Strike.is, made by Freakinware Studios.

Or Freakinware Limited. Fitting, as their Game Developing Career is indeed, [i]Limited[/i].

[h1]Did they make anything Unique?[/h1]

Let me answer that as simply as possible.

[b]F*CK NO![/b]

Freakinware also made games like "Mitos.is" and "Worm.is" Both [b]CLEAR COPIES[/b] of the Hit browser games such as Agar.io and Slither.io.

Let me give you the Rundown of the games "made" by Freakinware.

[list]
   [*] Mitos.is = [url=Agar.io]Agar.io[/url]
   [*] Worm.is = [url=Slither.io]Slither.io[/url]
   [*] Strike.is = [url=Diep.io]Diep.io[/url]
[/list]
(All are Browser games. Please, play those instead of this.)

Every game they claim to be original are DAMN NEAR FACIMILES. (Facimile, an exact copy.)
The only f*cking Difference with these games are Pets, Microtransactions, and Free-use Dubstep.

To think these [strike]C*nts[/strike] are making [b]MONEY[/b] off these piles of Wank [b]BAFFLES ME![/b]

[h1]What about the Game itself? What's the Gameplay like?[/h1]

Honestly, I couldn't tell you. Like i said in the Disclaimer, i simply Downloaded this game to insult the people that Published it. I Recommend you read the reviews of people who TRIED to play this.

[h1]How can you be sure Diep.io didn't copy Strike.is?[/h1]

Because i PERSONALLY PLAYED Diep.io BEFORE this got on Steam, BEFORE Popular Youtubers (Such as Markiplier, Jacksepticeye, ETC.) played Diep.io. After that, POOF, Strike.is appeared on Greenlight.

Can't wait for Hatfilms to say this is Better that Diep.io... Ugh.

[h1]Why are you making this Review?[/h1]

It [i][b]sucks[/b][/i] when your ideas get stolen. When your stolen ideas earn [i]money for the thiefs,[/i] That's just worse.

[h1]The Conclusion[/h1]

This game doesn't DESERVE an Out-of-10 rating.

Go play Diep.io instead.

review:
After making a rip-off of agar.io with Mitos.is, and copying slither.io with worm.is, this time it's diep.io with strike.is!

It may also be a rip-off of Vertix.io, but it seems more like diep.io, those two are quite similar. One has level up and stats, the other, classes. 

The only differences between Strike.is and Diep.io / Vertix.io ? Ugly graphics, full of microtransactions. 

I wonder which .io game they will copy next, I'm on the edge of my seat!

This game also contain their two other games; it's basically the same launcher with three store pages.
